label.value: transcriptional regulatory protein PhoP isoform 1

value.value: A transcriptional regulatory protein PhoP that is a translation product of some mRNA whose exon structure and start site selection renders it capable of giving rise to a protein with the amino acid sequence represented by UniProtKB:P23836-1 or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.

label.value: transcriptional regulatory protein PhoP isoform 1 unmodified form

value.value: A transcriptional regulatory protein PhoP isoform 1 that has not been subjected to any co- or post-translational residue modification or peptide bond cleavage.

label.value: transcriptional regulatory protein PhoP isoform 1 phosphorylated 1

value.value: A transcriptional regulatory protein PhoP isoform 1 that has been phosphorylated by phosphorylated phoQ on the conserved Asp residue within the receiver domain. Example: UniProtKB:P23836-1, Asp-51, MOD:00042.

label.value: S-adenosylmethionine synthetase isoform 1, initiator methionine removed acetylated 1

value.value: An S-adenosylmethionine synthetase isoform 1, initiator methionine removed form that has been acetylated at the position equivalent to Lys-3 of the amino acid sequence represented by UniProtKB:P0A817-1. Example: UniProtKB:P0A817-1, 2-384, Lys-3, MOD:00064.

label.value: superoxide dismutase [Fe] isoform 1, initiator methionine removed acetylated 1

value.value: A superoxide dismutase [Fe] isoform 1, initiator methionine removed form that has been acetylated at the position equivalent to Lys-51 of the amino acid sequence represented by UniProtKB:P0AGD3-1. Example: UniProtKB:P0AGD3-1, 2-193, Lys-51, MOD:00064.

label.value: sensor protein TorS isoform 1 phosphorylated 3

value.value: A sensor protein TorS isoform 1 that has been phosphorylated by transfer of a phosphoryl group from a His residue in the N-terminal transmitter domain to an Asp residue within the receiver domain. Example: UniProtKB:P39453-1, Asp-733, MOD:00042.

label.value: torCAD operon transcriptional regulatory protein TorR isoform 1

value.value: A torCAD operon transcriptional regulatory protein TorR that is a translation product of some mRNA whose exon structure and start site selection renders it capable of giving rise to a protein with the amino acid sequence represented by UniProtKB:P38684-1 or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.

label.value: torCAD operon transcriptional regulatory protein TorR isoform 1 phosphorylated 1

value.value: A torCAD operon transcriptional regulatory protein TorR isoform 1 that has been phosphorylated on the conserved Asp residue within the receiver domain. Example: UniProtKB:P38684-1, Asp-53, MOD:00042.

definition.value: Category=modification. Note: This proteoform activates transcription of torCAD.
